8. Use Container Widget with margin property in Flutter App Development

✅ Explanation (Exam-Oriented)

The Container widget in Flutter uses the margin property to add space outside the container.
It creates distance between the container and surrounding widgets.

Margin is defined using EdgeInsets
Helps in proper spacing and layout design

//main code


import 'package:flutter/material.dart';

void main() {
  runApp(MyApp());
}

class MyApp extends StatelessWidget {
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return MaterialApp(
      home: ContainerMarginExample(),
    );
  }
}

class ContainerMarginExample extends StatelessWidget {
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return Scaffold(
      appBar: AppBar(
        title: Text("Container Margin Example"),
      ),
      body: Center(
        child: Container(
          margin: EdgeInsets.all(30),
          height: 100,
          width: 200,
          color: Colors.orange,
          child: Center(
            child: Text(
              "With Margin",
              style: TextStyle(color: Colors.white, fontSize: 18),
            ),
          ),
        ),
      ),
    );
  }
}